1.2.1	It sounds like a power issue to me.	St
1.2.2	Do you have a surge protector between the computer and the wall outlet?	St
1.2.3	You may want to try a UPS (Uninterruptable Power Supply) to see if you are getting voltage dips/spikes.	St
1.2.4	If you do get a UPS, make sure the voltage rating is sufficient for your computer and don't plug your printer, especially laser printers, into it.	St
1.2.5	If that doesn't remedy the problem, you have either a faulty power supply or mobo.	St
